description.narrative: National systems are strengthened to provide integrated health, nutrition, and early childhood interventions and services., which contributes to Child Health, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The most vulnerable children and their families access improved quality and equitable health, nutrition and early intervention services
